   "body" : "What I've noticed now that transaction rates are getting much higher is that every time a block is downloaded during the initial sync, sometimes 5, 10 or more new transactions are being downloaded as well and is slowing down the initial sync process.  There is no reason to do a \"getdata\" and download these transactions since they are not getting accepted into the mempool anyway.",
